OL,5,G0000 Face to Face with David Hockney
OL,6,     FIn an interview first broadcast in
OL,7,     F1996, artist David Hockney talks
OL,8,     Fto Jeremy Isaacs about painting,
OL,9,     Fdesigning for the opera and his
OL,10,     Fgrowing deafness.
OL,11,G0040 American Visions
OL,12,     F6/8. Robert Hughes considers
OL,13,     FAmerica during the 1920s and 30s,
OL,14,     Fincluding the skyscraper as the
OL,15,     Fimage of modernism, the
OL,16,     FDepression, regionalist art and
OL,17,     Fblack art.
